-- Carter Scores Three as Kings Defeat Coyotes 4-0 in NHL Playoffs
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-05-16T04:22:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/carter-scores-three-as-kings-defeat-coyotes-4-0-in-nhl-playoffs.html
Jeff Carter scored three goals and
goalie Jonathan Quick stopped 24 shots for his third career
playoff shutout as the Los Angeles Kings defeated the Phoenix
Coyotes 4-0 to lead their National Hockey League playoff series
two games to none.  The winner of the best-of-seven Western Conference finals
will play the  New York Rangers  or the  New Jersey Devils  in the
Stanley Cup Final.  Dwight King scored his fourth goal of the playoffs in the
first period at Jobing.com Arena in Glendale, Arizona. Carter
added two goals in the second period and another in the third.  The Kings, who are 7-0 on the road this postseason, host
the Coyotes tomorrow with Game 4 following on May 20, also in
Los Angeles.  Tonight, the Rangers host the Devils in Game 2 of the
Eastern Conference finals.  New York  won the series opener 3-0.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
